ZCZC GE56
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
WEDNESDAY TO SATURDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 062300 UTC
ON WEDNESDAY EVENING LOW PRESSURE WILL BE CENTRED NEAR SOLE 1007. THIS
WILL MOV SLWY NEWARDS WITH LITTLE CHANGE TO BE CENTRED OVER NERN IRELAND
BY MIDDAY THURSDAY THEN OVER SCOTLAND BY MIDDAY FRIDAY. IT WILL THEN BE
CENTRED OVER SERN NORWAY BY MIDDAY SATURDAY. IN THE MEANTIME A RIDGE OF HIGH
PRESSURE WILL EXTEND FM MID-ATLANTIC BETWEEN ICELAND AND THE FAEROES. THE
HIGH WILL THEN DRIFT NEWARDS TO BE CENTRED JUST W OF BAILEY BY MIDDAY THURSDAY
BEFORE RETREATING AWAY SWWARDS AGAIN DURING FRIDAY. IT WILL THEN RE-FORM
JUST W OF ROCKALL DURING SATURDAY. DURING FRIDAY LOW PRESSURE IN MID-ATLANTIC
WILL MOV SEWARDS TO BECOME SLOW MOV JUST W OF FITZROY DURING SATURDAY. NEAR
GALES ARE POSS IN NERN AREAS MAINLY VIKING AND N UTSIRE ON SATURDAY. STRG
WINDS ARE POSS IN FAIR ISLE ON THURSDAY AND FRIDAY. OTHERWISE NO HAZARDOUS
WINDS ARE EXP DURING THIS PERIOD
